cdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1622<br> <font color=#333333>(7/5/02 4:35:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=61>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Frenzied Burnout</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> FB doesnt need any longer duration, 36 seconds is long enuff to make it usefull for the same fights MB is usefull.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Demonstrably false.<br>
<br>
Assume that the net effect of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Frenzied Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> was to double damage output for 36 seconds.<br>
<br>
First, you could simply let the pet live and fight another 36 seconds, and deal the same amount of damage without any AA ability at all.  Indeed, if the fight lasts longer than 72 seconds after using this ability, you get less damage if you use this ability.  <br>
<br>
Second, under normal circumstances, a pet does 20-35 DPS, let's be generous, and call it 30 DPS.  Doubling that for 36 seconds yield another 1080 damage, comparable to a single cast of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shock of Fiery Blades</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and hardly comparable to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Manaburn</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Even manaless, I could use <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Boots of Bladecalling</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for two casts at 600 damage each.<br>
<br>
Third, actual log analysis reveals that most of the time a pet under <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Frenzied Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> deals <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>less</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> damage than without it, and the rest of the time the increased damage is of dubious statistical significance.<br>
<br>
Bottom line: at 36 seconds duration, even fixed, even with the supposed explosion, the increased damage is insignificant, less than two or three casts of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shock of Fiery Blades</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
We need a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>real</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Improved Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> skill that lasts a decent amount of time.  Unless <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Frenzied Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> at least quadruples damage output for its 36 second duration, it is a cruel joke, and an insult to the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> who trusted <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and invested hundreds of hours of their time obtaining the skill.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Master ArchMage Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
