<br>
Jokingly in guild chat the other day, we got to talking about FB...kinda weird considering how few mages we have that actually talk..anyways...and someone suggested FB turning out pet into basically Vindicator level damage for the duration.  The weirdest thing was...it was a monk that said it.  Just about every class realizes the screw job we got with AA abilities.  So i say make frenzied burnout turn our pet into a great melee, raise the atk of our pets so they can actually hurt luclin AC mobs and see what we can do for once.  Give raid leaders a reason to actually want us to have a pet on the final boss encounter (long...angry story omitted).<br>
<br>
As for the referenced Turn Summoned.  Unless you like goofing off in the hole, the spell is useless.  There needs to be an addition of more summoned mobs, or the flagging of more mobs as summoned.  SoR is the only useful summoned procing weapons we can give a pet, yet there is virtually nothing to kill with it.<br>
