The necro 'big damage' AA, lifeburn, requires no mana, but even the most disgustingly well equipped, hp-laden necromancer can only squeeze ~5khp damage out of it, with full raid buffs. Essentially it's a free 4-5k damage nuke every 72 minutes, provided you can manage the aggro. The above mentioned pet is... slightly better than lifeburn, manaburn, and perhaps deathtouch <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If the stats were simply off the top of your mind, I fully understand. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udrashtheardark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drash Theardark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(7/20/02 11:16:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=70>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Eeeek!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If there were an Expburn instead of a Manaburn, wouldn't it still give wizards a super nuke for raids, yet also reduce the casual use of this nuke?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
